The scientific method has been developed over time. Aristotle (an Ancient Greek philosopher) was the first person
to realise that theories needed to be based on observations. Muslim scholars then introduced the ideas of creating
a hypothesis, testing it, and repeating your work to check your results. And a chap called Roger Bacon later
developed things further by writing down everything he did, so other scientists could try to reproduce his work.
